verses.verse: Then the swollen waters Would have gone over our soul.‚Äù
Blessed be the LORD, Who has not given us as prey to their teeth.
(Num. 16:30; Ps. 56:1, 2; 57:3; Prov. 1:12) Our soul has escaped (Ps. 91:3) as a bird from the snare of the fowlers; The snare is broken, and we have escaped.
(Prov. 6:5; Hos. 9:8) Our help is in the name of the LORD, ((Ps. 121:2)) Who made heaven and earth.
The LORD the Strength of His People A Song of Ascents. [1] Those who trust in the LORD Are like Mount Zion, Which cannot be moved, but abides forever.
As the mountains surround Jerusalem, So the LORD surrounds His people From this time forth and forever.
